   <conbody>
      <p class="- topic/p ">For the protective earth (PE) cables sizes it is recommended to
follow the table below based on IEC 62477-1:2012. The table only lists
recommended minimum size. Always follow applicable local and/or national
electrical codes.</p>
      <p class="- topic/p ">The size of the protective earth cable depends on the size of the
used power cables. For the recommended minimum size of the power cables,
see the chapter <xref href="Recommended_Power_Cable_Dimensions_CPT_0000468445.dita"
               scope="local"
               type="concept"
               class="- topic/xref "/>.</p>
      <note type="important" class="- topic/note ">The calculated values assume the PE cable is
made of the same material as the power cable. If the material is different,
the PE cross-section area needs to be determined so that the conductance
is equivalent to the result from the table.</note>
      <note class="- topic/note ">The calculated values are only for cross-sectional areas in
mm<sup class="+ topic/ph hi-d/sup ">2</sup>. If the power cable size is specified in AWG or kcmil
convert to mm<sup class="+ topic/ph hi-d/sup ">2</sup> and use the table, then convert back to
AWG or kcmil.</note>
